# Anaj Bahi - environment configuration
#
# The PWA (frontend/) is a LOCAL-ONLY offline app and needs NO secrets and NO .env.
# Run it with:  cd frontend && pnpm install && pnpm dev
#
# The ONLY component that needs configuration is the optional cloud-sync/backup
# backend (FastAPI + SQLite, under backend/). Its variables live in backend/.env
# (copy backend/.env.example -> backend/.env). They are documented there, and are:
#
#   DATABASE_URL=sqlite:///./data/anaj.db     # single-file SQLite DB (no DB server)
#   DEVICE_TOKEN=change-me-to-a-long-random-string   # shared secret gating /sync/*
#
# The app sends the same DEVICE_TOKEN (entered in Settings -> Cloud backup) as a
# Bearer token. backend/.env is gitignored; only backend/.env.example is committed.
